    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@a11r: Obviously not exactly the same case, but ideal memory allocation growth rate is the golden ratio:\n- http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1100311/what-is-the-ideal-growth-rate-for-a-dynamically-allocated-array\n- http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5232198/about-vectors-growth\n- https://crntaylor.wordpress.com/2011/07/15/optimal-memory-reallocation-and-the-golden-ratio/\n\nAlso, it has the nice feature of being pretty close to the current numbers (~1.5%), while gaining a nice mathematical property.  Programmers like nerdy math stuff typically; using these numbers reinforces that gRPC was written with care. \n"
  },
